os-fleet-agent — push-mode agent for the os-fleet
multi-OPNsense management platform.

Periodically collects local system status (firmware, plugins,
certificates, firewall configuration) from this OPNsense and ships it
to a configured os-fleet server via outbound HTTPS. No inbound
connections to this box are required: ideal for OPNsense instances
behind NAT, dynamic IPs, or strict customer-side firewalls.

WWW: https://github.com/KaiOppi/os-fleet-agent
